Allow representing deleted entities similar to added/changed entities


    {
      "@odata.context":"#Orders/$entity",
      "@odata.id":"Orders(10643)",
      "ShippingAddress":{
        "Street":"23 Tsawassen Blvd.",
        "City":"Tsawassen",
        "Region":"BC",
        "PostalCode":"T2F 8M4"
      },
    },
    {
      "@odata.context":"#Customers/$entityDeletion",
      "@odata.id":"Customers('ANTON')",
      "@odata.reason":"deleted",
      /* optionally properties of the deleted entity */
     "CustomerID": "ANTON",
     ...
    }

This would allow using the same serialization template. And it looks more consistent :-)

Do this in conjunction with conformance, so clients have a way to determine which optional parts of 4.01 are supported by a service.

Things already covered:
 * POST/PATCH/PUT with system query options to shape response:Â ODATA-1216
 * $select with nested query options:Â ODATA-1176
 * $compute with insert/update: ODATA-1216
 * Deep update:Â {{DeepUpdateSupport}}

Things covered by the referenced pull request:
 - Upsert:Â {{UpdateRestrictions/Upsertable}}
 - PATCH on collection using delta format:Â {{UpdateRestrictions/DeltaUpdateSupported}}
 - PATCH with filter path segment: {{UpdateRestrictions/FilterSegmentSupported}}
 - PATCH with typecast segment: {{UpdateRestrictions/TypecastSegmentSupported}}
